title: Sudan's military seize power in coup
content: Protesters in Khartoum denounce the coup, as soldiers cut off main roads and restrict the internet.

title: Saudi prince suggested killing king - ex-official
content: Mohammed bin Salman discussed assassinating the late King Abdullah in 2014, Saad al-Jabri says.

title: Abducted cable car crash boy to be returned to Italy
content: The six-year-old survivor of a cable car crash must be returned to his aunt in Italy, a court rules.

title: Baldwin was pointing gun at camera on film set
content: Legal papers shed light on what happened when actor Alec Baldwin fired a gun with tragic results.

title: Israeli cabinet backs huge spending plan for Arabs
content: Billions of dollars are earmarked for Israel's Arab minority, which has long complained of neglect.

title: Afghan baby girl sold for $500 by starving family
content: The BBC’s Yogita Limaye witnesses first-hand the extreme poverty engulfing millions in Afghanistan.

title: German IS woman jailed for Yazidi girl's death
content: A Munich court jails a jihadi bride for 10 years for the agonising death of a Yazidi girl in 2015.
